<subSubSection id="72F842B85A38CDAD1F46A03AFBC4B883" pageId="16" pageNumber="185" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="FBD6BEACB0F2E3DED59CF299A55B1E73" pageId="16" pageNumber="185">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="01EBD1A755D4A1F664E61561FF5B9FFD" pageId="16" pageNumber="185">
The examination of the type of 
<taxonomicName id="647286F44FBB2FD868EDFF4A83DBC460" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Alphitobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Alphitobius opacus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opacus">Alphitobius opacus</taxonomicName>
Gerstaecker, 1871 shows, that the original assignment to 
<taxonomicName id="AC3BD7F9F2E375F4DEFA63090095FA1B" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Alphitobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Alphitobius" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Alphitobius</taxonomicName>
is wrong and that this species must be transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="9AD12088948F178EB03F72617F61C29A" authority="Laporte, 1833" authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1833" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Peltoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Peltoides" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Peltoides</taxonomicName>
Laporte, 1832, subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="1D5C7FFEA997D31CE26DD49384277287" authority="Pic, 1916" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Micropeltoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Micropeltoides" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Micropeltoides</taxonomicName>
Pic, 1916, because of entirely different body shape, different shape of antennomeres, and different shape of male genitalia with the base of basale not asymmetrical as in 
<taxonomicName id="F8380438F4F3F5BB63874D18E53DD39E" lsidName="" pageId="16" pageNumber="185" rank="tribe" tribe="Alphitobiini">Alphitobiini</taxonomicName>
. The type of 
<taxonomicName id="C03ABB5EAB3CCEB1A5DFCFB7C3443520" authority="Laporte, 1833" authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1833" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Peltoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Peltoides (Micropeltoides) crypticoides" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crypticoides" subGenus="Micropeltoides">Peltoides (Micropeltoides) crypticoides</taxonomicName>
Pic, 1916 fully coincide with opacus, and is thus a junior synonym.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F6AD097CB01A50078152FEEA6571B7DA" pageId="16" pageNumber="185" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5D04DEF652A9493C0EAE519CFF4AE2B5" pageId="16" pageNumber="185">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D53CACCA2DD4E8FE72525D33A4DECCE8" pageId="16" pageNumber="185">
Tanzania (type locality opacus), Central African Republic (type locality of crypticoides); Senegal (
<bibRefCitation id="63F733AD11A37309CB0000F7F2696AB9" author="Ardoin, P" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de l'Institut francais d'Afrique noire (A)" pageId="17" pageNumber="186" pagination="1374 - 1387" title="Contribution a l'etude de la faune de la basse Casamance (Senegal) VI." volume="25" year="1963 b">Ardoin 1963b</bibRefCitation>
), Ivory Coast (
<bibRefCitation id="29458AF41A78570AB9E46FC62C70C9C9" author="Ardoin, P" journalOrPublisher="Annales du Musee royale de l'Afrique centrale (serie Zoologie)" pageId="17" pageNumber="186" pagination="139 - 285" title="Contribution a la connaissance de la faune entomologique de la Cote-d'Ivoire (J. Decelle, 1961 - 1964). XXXVII. Coleoptera Tenebrionidae." volume="175" year="1969">Ardoin 1969</bibRefCitation>
), Mali, The Gambia (
<bibRefCitation id="6527FC545B4915A138CD5520DD4F4A04" author="Grimm, R" journalOrPublisher="Entomofauna" pageId="17" pageNumber="186" pagination="353 - 380" title="Tenebrionidae von Gambia (Insecta, Coleoptera)." volume="23" year="2002">Grimm 2002</bibRefCitation>
, all under 
<taxonomicName id="DCC3917CBFC9A070B39D92863540201A" authority="Laporte, 1833" authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1833" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Peltoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Peltoides (Micropeltoides) crypticoides" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crypticoides" subGenus="Micropeltoides">Peltoides (Micropeltoides) crypticoides</taxonomicName>
); Benin, Cameroon, Guinea, Uganda, Angola, Zambia (new records).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
